problem_statement:
Signal effect does not trigger when value changes to null
There seems to be a bug in the change tracking that prevents effects from triggering when the value of a `ValueSignal` changes from a non-null value to `null`.

This unit test would fail:
```java
@Test
void changeTracking_changeValueToNull_effectTriggered() {
    ValueSignal<String> signal = new ValueSignal<>("initial");
    ArrayList<String> invocations = new ArrayList<>();

    Signal.effect(() -> {
        invocations.add(signal.value());
    });

    assertEquals(Arrays.asList("initial"), invocations);

    signal.value(null);
    assertEquals(Arrays.asList("initial", null), invocations);
}
```

