problem_statement:
ComboBox with AbstractBackEndDataProvider - Query pageSize always null
### Description

I have noticed that, when using a `ComboBox` with an `AbstractBackEndDataProvider`, the `Query` object in `fetchFromBackEnd` never has `pageSize` set, which causes it to always default to `limit`.

This was an issue in my current Project, where my `AbstractBackEndDataProvider` implementation queries a `JpaRepository` with a `Pageable` Object. In order to instantiate this object I need the pageNumber and pageSize, which I can't properly compute without explicitly having a pageSize.

The issue would namely occur when the DataProvider would fetch the last page. Say we have 27 entries and a pageSize set to 20:
- The first page would be fetched without a an issue: in Query, `limit` it set to 20 (and therefore `getPage()=20` also). 
- The problem occurs once we scroll down; a second query is executed, this time with `limit` is 7 (and therefore `getPageSize()` returns 7), and so if I try to instantiate the corresponding PageRequest, I am forced to use `pageNumber = offset / pageSize = 20 / 7 = 2` which is wrong, as we are querying for the second page, and not the third. 

This would cause some values in the dropdown to be displayed twice, and some to not be displayed. See image belowm, here we would expect to see "String 1" to "String 27". This corresponds to the snippet in the "Minimal reproducible example" section:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f78a742c-70c4-45ae-90af-5d9041dce520)

The workaround I built in our code consisted in extending my implementation of the `AbstractBackEndDataProvider` in order to remember the `pageSize` set in the `ComboBox`. Maybe I am not aware of all details, but it seems to me it would be better to have `DataComunicator#doFetchFromDataProvider` setting the pageSize to the instantiated `Query` object.

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4dc681dc-40ef-4711-a1e9-2f7bae35815f)

### Expected outcome

I would expect the input `Query` parameter of `AbstractBackEndDataProvider#fetchFromBackEnd` to have the pageSize set to the set `pageSize` value in the ComboBox, and not the `limit` of the current query.

### Minimal reproducible example

```
class SomeDataProvider extends AbstractBackEndDataProvider<String, String> {

    private final List<String> listOfStrings = new ArrayList<>();

    public SomeDataProvider() {
        for (int i = 1; i <= 27; i++) {
            listOfStrings.add("String " + i);
        }
    }

    /**
     * This simulates what a JpaQuery would do.
     */
    private Stream<String> fetchPage(int pageNumber, int pageSize) {
        int calculateOffset = pageNumber * pageSize;
        return listOfStrings.subList(calculateOffset, Math.min(calculateOffset + pageSize, listOfStrings.size())).stream();
    }

    @Override
    protected Stream<String> fetchFromBackEnd(Query<String, String> query) {
        System.out.println("pageSize : " + query.getPageSize());
        System.out.println("limit : " + query.getLimit());
        int pageNumber = query.getOffset() / query.getPageSize();
        return fetchPage(pageNumber, query.getPageSize());
    }

    @Override
    protected int sizeInBackEnd(Query<String, String> query) {
        return listOfStrings.size();
    }
}

ComboBox<String> comboBox = new ComboBox<>();
comboBox.setPageSize(20);
comboBox.setDataProvider(new SomeDataProvider(), SerializableFunction.identity());
```

### Steps to reproduce

1. Add the ComboBox described above to a view
2. Open the ComboBox dropdown and scroll to the bottom
3. The last few elements cannot be seen. Additionally, in the logs see how the following values are logged:
pageSize : 20
limit : 20
pageSize : 7
limit : 7

### Environment

Vaadin version(s): 24.6.7 and 24.7.3
OS: Windows 10
Spring-Boot: 3.4.4

### Browsers

Firefox

