problem_statement:
UploadHandler method overrides are ignored by Upload
### Description of the bug

Upload handler's methods overrides are ignored in Upload, e.g. custom url prefix and other default methods in UploadHandler are not taken into account, e.g. this doesn't use custom postfix:
```java
        InMemoryUploadHandler inMemoryUploadHandler = new InMemoryUploadHandler(
                (uploadMetadata, bytes) -> {
                    // handle Uploaded data here
                }) {
            @Override
            public String getUrlPostfix() {
                return "custom-url-postfix";
            }

            // other overrides
        };
        upload.setUploadHandler(inMemoryUploadHandler);
```
This is because Upload wraps the original handler with calling component's methods before/after request handling:
```java
        UploadHandler newUploadHandler = event -> {
            try {
                startUpload();
                handler.handleUploadRequest(event);
            } finally {
                endUpload();
            }
        };
```

### Expected behavior

All overrides should be taken into account in request handling.

### Minimal reproducible example

See the example above

### Versions

- Vaadin / Flow version: 24.8.0.alpha8

